[3] Local news
- Thu 31 Jan 2019. Women journalists
[Radio Moto Butembo-Beni, online trans., abridged, edited]
http://radiomotofm.info/lirearticle.php?billet=5373

In Butembo, women journalists pledge to accompany Ebola response teams. Women gathered in the Congolese Union of Media Women made this commitment at the end of their meeting around the theme "The role of the female journalist in the fight against the Ebola virus disease." This is the theme that has nourished the UCOFEM-Butembo exchange, this Thu 31 Jan 2019.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Mary Marshall

[This is an excellent idea, as women may be able to make a stronger connection than men are able to accomplish, with the locals. - Mod.LK]

- Thu 7 Feb 2019. Reports on "Resistance of the population against Ebola"
[Radio Moto Butembo-Beni, online trans., abridged, edited]
http://radiomotofm.info/lirearticle.php?billet=5405

Some recommendations have been made. Among other things, to increase the number of laboratories for a quick service when collecting samples, to consolidate the communication commission, to create transit centers because the patients are frustrated at Ebola treatment centers.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Mary Marshall

[This is the 1st time I have read that patients are frustrated at the treatment centers; I assume by the wait. The idea of transit centers might work well if rapid testing for Ebola virus could be done there. - Mod.LK

